    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-26T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-26T20:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2479a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-26T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 26, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>783. I called in the Japanese Ambassador and Mr. Kurusu in the afternoon of
                    November 26<note n="1" xml:id="d486fn1">See memorandum of November 26, 1941,
                            <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_764">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 764</ref>.</note> and gave them two
                    documents—an oral statement<note n="2" xml:id="d486fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_766">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 766</ref>.</note> and draft outline of
                    a proposed basis for a broad agreement covering the entire Pacific area.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d486fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_768">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 768</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>A summary of these documents follows in a subsequent telegram.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d486fn4">Telegram No. 784 of the same date, not printed; it was
                        repeated to the Ambassador in China as telegram No. 274.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
